The Rather Outdoors pickup is looking fine and fresh in the south !

So unbelievably thankful for this night. I was given the opportunity at this buck a few nights before but didn’t let one fly.  The second night we had him at 20 yards but he was standing behind a large brush patch, and with absolutely no shot opportunity. The third night is when all the magic happened . He was the last buck to jump the fence and gave me a short opportunity to seal the deal at 37 yards. Needless to say I let the Hoyt eat.  To be able to put an arrow though one of God’s most beautiful creatures is truly a blessing itself. It’s been a long time coming for me as it’s been about four years since I’ve harvested a deer with a bow . Between college , moving , and just not the right timing it finally came together tonight. God is good ✝️
Big thanks to @connor.brockhouse and @cadenbrockhouse  for helping me get it done! I Love you guys !

Got it done yesterday on a beautiful SD speed goat ! It’s been an incredible last few days for me with my bow.  Super blessed and thankful for the opportunities I have been given lately .
